-- UniCredit's HVB Backs Stress-Test Publication, Weimer Tells Handelsblatt
-- Christiane Lenzner
-- 2010-06-29T04:51:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/unicredit-s-hvb-backs-stress-test-publication-weimer-tells-handelsblatt.html

          
          
             Theodor Weimer, head of UniCredit
SpA’s German Hypovereinsbank unit, said the results of banking
stress tests should be published in a “clear, meaningful and
simple” way to support stability in financial markets,
according to an interview in Handelsblatt newspaper.  
          
          


  


        